# Backend Rules

## Folder Structure
server/
  main.py              # FastAPI app init, CORS, router registration
  routers/             # Route handlers only, no business logic
    chat.py            # Customer bot chat endpoint
    config.py          # Bot config read/write endpoints
    mistakes.py        # Mistakes CRUD endpoints
    meta_agent.py      # Manager meta-agent endpoint
  services/            # Business logic
    bot_service.py     # Customer bot logic, Gemini calls
    meta_service.py    # Meta-agent logic, config generation
    fix_service.py     # Auto-fix logic, guideline rewriting
    mock_tools.py      # getCardStatus(), getTransactionStatus()
  storage/             # JSON file read/write only
    config_store.py
    mistakes_store.py
  prompts/             # All prompt strings
    bot_prompt.py
    meta_prompt.py
    fix_prompt.py
  data/                # JSON data files (gitignored except templates)
    config.json
    mistakes.json

## FastAPI Rules
- Use async def for all route handlers
- Use Pydantic BaseModel for all request and response bodies
- Register all routers in main.py with prefix /api
- CORS must allow http://localhost:5173

## JSON Storage Rules
- config.json shape:
  {
    "kb_url": "",
    "kb_content": "",
    "system_prompt": "",
    "guidelines": [],
    "tools_enabled": ["getCardStatus", "getTransactionStatus"]
  }
- mistakes.json shape:
  {
    "open": [],
    "fixed": [],
    "archived": []
  }
- Each mistake shape:
  {
    "id": "uuid",
    "timestamp": "ISO string",
    "customer_message": "",
    "bot_response": "",
    "complaint_type": "",
    "comment": "",
    "status": "open|fixed|archived",
    "fix_diff": { "before": "", "after": "" }
  }
- Always read fresh from file on each request
- Always write atomically: write to .tmp file then rename

## Mock Tools
- getCardStatus(application_id) returns randomised status:
  pending | under_review | approved | rejected
- getTransactionStatus(transaction_id) returns randomised status:
  success | failed | processing | refunded
- Include realistic fields: dates, amounts, merchant names
- Seed randomisation with the ID so same ID always returns same result

## Gemini Rules
- Model: gemini-2.0-flash
- For customer bot: use function calling / tool use API
- For meta-agent: single prompt, expect JSON response
- For auto-fix: single prompt, expect JSON with before/after diff
- Always wrap Gemini calls in try/except
- Store API key in .env as GEMINI_API_KEY